,Recommended,261680,25328481,"Posted: 3 September, 2016",all,hoserama99,"Short, choose-your-own-adventure-ish type game. As with many indie games, this one has a heavy ending that slaps you in the face with drama. Sometimes that works, sometimes not. Here, it works.I say ""choose your own adventure"" but that's not quite right. You don't really influence the story outcome that I can tell, at least in any significant way. I'd have to do a second playthrough to know for sure, so take that for what it is.The game and artwork are as presented in the screenshots - you play the role of a girl with missing journal pages, and the story itself fills out over time as you learn more about what is going on.Gameplay-wise, I only ran into one bug: when streaming, the gamepad would not work on my Steam Link unless I unplugged the gamepad from my streaming machine. Once done, it was fully playable with the gamepad.The story is more interesting than it first lets on. I did have an urge to stop early on because it seemed a bit dull, but I'm glad I stuck it out. As time went on, I thought ""hey, I'm playing a truly bad girl who doesn't realize she's bad"". I would frequently be given choices that were, in a manner of speaking, all bad choices. That would have been a unique twist, but it wasn't the full story. In the end, it all made sense and I'm glad I stuck to it. My only complaint, I suppose, is that the game did feel a bit repetitive and long for what little gameplay and story there is.This may not be everyone's cup of tea, but it was a nice change of pace for me. Recommended 3 out of 5."
