76561198073600298,Recommended,261680,18322613,"Posted: 4 October, 2015",all,Legacy,"Follow a troubled teen who is trying to remember how her journal got erased, and fill in the blanks by just being alive.It's a visual novel if thats what you were wondering. No puzzles or anything to worry about. This means its very slow paced and relaxed, good for casual play.Simple controls, this casual game follows a young woman talking to friends, family and strangers to fill her journal with the missing information. Atleast, that what your objective starts out as.The art is simple and colourful, easy on the eyes and suits the game very well.Soon after finding your journal blank, you begin finding trouble and relationships are pushed. Depending on certain things you say, characters will treat you differently.The story seems to lose its focus and gets slightly confusing, having philosophical meanings and other behind the seen interpretations. It can be boring for the first 30 minutes or so until you get into the game and start progressing much faster. Has plenty of dialogue. Lots of reading too.Its easy, its casual and its simple.Grab it when its on sale, cause the price is pretty high for the very short 2 hour length and zero replayability. 10$ is incredibly overpriced. I got it on a 80% sale for 2$, I say do the same.Personal Rating: 2.5/5"
