76561198031911131,Recommended,261680,28693459,"Posted: 26 December, 2016",all,gricomet,Beautifully illustrated visual novel game about a girl dealing with personal life troubles. It is an interesting world to walk through as you go through the days of her life and the journal she records it. You primarily follow the story by walking around her home town with occassional dialogue choices. If you like the visual novel approach this certainly would have appeal to you.
,Recommended,261680,13973578,"Posted: 13 January, 2015",all,Arch Enemy,"Simple Yet ProfoundJournal is a very deep, interesting, story driven game that revolves around a teenage protagonist's life struggle and it's up to you to help her get through them by interacting with other characters, learning more about them and herself as you progress and choosing what happens next. You can be supportive and understanding or bitter and resentful, which means you make decisions that affect the narrative. How much of an impact it has on the final outcome is yet to be seen as I have yet to replay the game and chances are I will. I very much enjoy the story, the characters and the overall presentation of the game and I'm having a lot of fun with it. I can't say more without spoiling it for others, butI really recommend this game for anyone remotely interested in a good story."
76561198091433703,Recommended,261680,31212846,Posted: 17 April,all,KatieLou1122,"Really great game! I really felt like I was back in high school lol. The ending made me cry a little I won't lie. One of those ""this all makes sense now"" moments. Pick it up! You won't regret it!"
,Recommended,261680,35277495,Posted: 28 September,all,Chungus,"Bought this on a steam sale for $2It has a really touching story. It is unclear what is happening at some stages but you slowly piece things together and it is a story about friendship, loss, betrayal and learning to move on and accept things that have happened.Really confused by the negative reviews. Before playing I saw some negative reviews that honed in on the things the protagonist did that were bad. It is explained why she did some bad things in the story and despite not liking some of her choices of dialogue, she's not meant to be a perfect protagonist. Sometimes she says and does things you don't agree with or like but that's okay since it is her story. We are seeing this story through the eyes of the protagonist so I think it is more interesting if the character isn't someone exactly like me.Overall, I recommend this game as I think it tackles the subjects really well and it is a good story based game. It is mild in regards to the actualy ""gameplay"" aspects but if you like the interactive ""choose your own story"" kinds of games I think you will like this."
